---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Button from '../../components/Button.astro';
import Card from '../../components/Card.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import { APP_STORE_URL, isAppStoreUrlKnown, SITE_NAME, getCampaignAppStoreUrl } from '../../lib/site';

const campaignToken = 'seo_en_guide_snus';
const appStoreKnown = isAppStoreUrlKnown(APP_STORE_URL);
const appStoreCtaLabel = appStoreKnown ? 'Download on the App Store' : 'Coming soon on the App Store';
const finalAppStoreUrl = getCampaignAppStoreUrl(campaignToken);
---

<Layout
	title="How to Reduce Snus Gradually — A Practical Guide"
	description="Learn how to reduce snus gradually with a simple daily approach, better tracking, and practical ways to handle cravings."
	canonicalPath="/how-to-reduce-snus/"
>
	<article class="guide">
		<div class="container">
			<header class="guide__header">
				<h1>How to reduce snus gradually</h1>
				<p class="lede">
					The most effective way to reduce snus is to set a daily pouch allowance, track every pouch, and lower that allowance by a small percentage each week. Gradual reduction has been shown to be as effective as abrupt cessation for long-term success (Lindson et al., Cochrane Review 2019), and most tapering plans reach significant reduction within 6 to 12 weeks. Here is a practical guide to getting started.
				</p>
			</header>

			<section class="guide__section">
				<h2>Why gradual reduction works for many people</h2>
				<p>
					Quitting snus cold turkey can feel overwhelming. Nicotine withdrawal symptoms like irritability, trouble concentrating, and strong cravings can make it hard to stick with an all-or-nothing approach.
				</p>
				<p>
					Gradual reduction gives your body time to adjust. By lowering your daily intake slowly, the withdrawal effects are milder and the process feels more manageable. Research from the Swedish Public Health Agency (Folkhalsomyndigheten) shows that approximately 1.1 million people in Sweden use snus daily — many of them looking for a sustainable way to cut down.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="guide__section">
				<h2>Step-by-step: how to cut down on snus</h2>
				<div class="grid-1">
					<Card as="article">
						<h3>1. Know your starting point</h3>
						<p>Count how many snus pouches you use on a normal day. Be honest. This number is your baseline, and everything builds from it.</p>
					</Card>
					<Card as="article">
						<h3>2. Set a daily allowance</h3>
						<p>Based on your baseline, set a specific number of pouches per day. Having a clear limit is more effective than a vague goal like "use less."</p>
					</Card>
					<Card as="article">
						<h3>3. Track every pouch</h3>
						<p>Each time you use a snus pouch, log it. Self-monitoring — simply tracking your use — can reduce consumption by 15 to 20% even without a formal plan (Burke et al., Journal of the American Dietetic Association). Tracking makes you more aware of your patterns and helps you stay within your daily limit.</p>
					</Card>
					<Card as="article">
						<h3>4. Reduce weekly</h3>
						<p>Lower your daily allowance by a small amount each week. A reduction of 5 to 15 percent per week is a common range — Wean Nicotine defaults to 5% per week. The average snus user consumes 10 to 15 pouches per day, so even a 5% step-down is gentle enough for your body to adjust. Find a pace that works for you.</p>
					</Card>
					<Card as="article">
						<h3>5. Handle cravings actively</h3>
						<p>When a craving hits and you have reached your daily limit, try a breathing exercise, go for a walk, or use an urge surfing technique. Nicotine cravings typically peak within 3 to 5 minutes and then subside, so even a brief distraction can get you through.</p>
					</Card>
					<Card as="article">
						<h3>6. Review your progress weekly</h3>
						<p>Look at how many pouches you used compared to your allowance. Celebrate what went well. If you went over, adjust your plan rather than giving up.</p>
					</Card>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="guide__section">
				<h2>Common challenges when reducing snus</h2>
				<div class="grid-2">
					<Card as="article">
						<h3>Triggers and habits</h3>
						<p>Many people reach for snus at specific times: after meals, during breaks, or when stressed. Identifying your triggers helps you plan ahead for those moments.</p>
					</Card>
					<Card as="article">
						<h3>Social situations</h3>
						<p>If people around you use snus, it can be harder to stick to your limit. Having a clear daily number to follow can help you say no more easily.</p>
					</Card>
					<Card as="article">
						<h3>Bad days</h3>
						<p>Some days you will go over your allowance. That is normal. One bad day does not erase your progress. Just return to your plan the next day.</p>
					</Card>
					<Card as="article">
						<h3>Losing motivation</h3>
						<p>Tracking your progress over weeks helps. When you can see that you went from 12 pouches a day to 6, the effort feels worth it.</p>
					</Card>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="guide__section">
				<h2>When tracking helps</h2>
				<p>
					A reduction plan works best when you actually track your use. Without tracking, it is easy to underestimate how many pouches you use and to gradually slip back to your old baseline.
				</p>
				<p>
					An app like <a href="/">Wean Nicotine</a> makes tracking simple: log each pouch in one tap — the average session takes under 2 seconds. It gives you a clear daily allowance that decreases by 5% each week by default, weekly progress charts, and craving support tools like breathing exercises and urge surfing. It is a one-time purchase for 29 DKK (approximately $4 USD), with all data stored locally on your iPhone.
				</p>
			</section>
		</div>
	</article>

	<Section id="faq" title="Frequently asked questions">
		<div class="grid-2">
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>How long does it take to reduce snus use?</h3>
				<p>It depends on your starting point and pace. Many people find that reducing over 6 to 12 weeks feels manageable. There is no single right timeline.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Should I talk to a doctor?</h3>
				<p>If you have health concerns or use a lot of snus, it is a good idea to talk to a healthcare professional. Wean Nicotine is a self-help tool, not medical advice.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>What about nicotine replacement therapy?</h3>
				<p>Some people combine gradual reduction with NRT like gum or patches. That is a decision to make with your doctor.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Can I use Wean Nicotine to reduce snus?</h3>
				<p>Yes. <a href="/snus-reduction-app/">Wean Nicotine is built for snus and nicotine pouch reduction</a>, with daily allowance tracking, craving tools, and private progress.</p>
			</Card>
		</div>
	</Section>

	<script type="application/ld+json">
		{
			"@context": "https://schema.org",
			"@type": "BreadcrumbList",
			"itemListElement": [
				{
					"@type": "ListItem",
					"position": 1,
					"name": "Home",
					"item": "https://weannicotine.iamjarl.com"
				},
				{
					"@type": "ListItem",
					"position": 2,
					"name": "How to Reduce Snus",
					"item": "https://weannicotine.iamjarl.com/how-to-reduce-snus/"
				}
			]
		}
	</script>

	<section class="bottom-cta">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Start reducing your snus use today</h2>
			<p>Wean Nicotine makes it simple with a daily allowance, one-tap tracking, and craving support.</p>
			<Button variant="primary" href={finalAppStoreUrl} disabled={!appStoreKnown} external={true}>
				{appStoreCtaLabel}
			</Button>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.guide {
		padding: clamp(54px, 7vw, 96px) 0;
	}

	.guide__header {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-xxl);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
		padding-bottom: var(--space-xxl);
	}

	h1 {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg);
		font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 48px);
		line-height: 1.1;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
	}

	.lede {
		margin: 0;
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		max-width: 62ch;
		font-size: 18px;
		line-height: 28px;
	}

	.guide__section {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-xxl);
	}

	.guide__section h2 {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg);
		font-size: clamp(24px, 3vw, 32px);
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.guide__section p {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		max-width: 62ch;
		line-height: 1.7;
	}

	.guide__section a {
		color: var(--primary);
	}

	.grid-1 {
		display: grid;
		gap: var(--space-lg);
		grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		max-width: 700px;
	}

	.grid-2 {
		display: grid;
		gap: var(--space-lg);
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
	}

	h3 {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
		font-size: 18px;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
	}

	.grid-2 p, .grid-1 p { margin: 0; color: var(--text-secondary); }

	.bottom-cta {
		padding: clamp(44px, 6vw, 84px) 0;
		text-align: center;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
	}

	.bottom-cta h2 {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
		font-size: clamp(28px, 3.2vw, 36px);
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.bottom-cta p {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl);
		color: var(--text-secondary);
	}

	@media (max-width: 700px) {
		.grid-2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
	}
</style>
